The Nigerian Navy on Wednesday alerted Nigerians on the activities of fraudsters currently operating fake online recruitment sites.A statement issued by the Navy's Director of Information, Suleiman Dahun, in Abuja, made this known.Mr. Dahun, a captain, said for the avoidance of doubt, the portal for registration of candidates for the 2017 NN Recruitment Exercise has not been opened."Therefore, innocent members of the public are advised to steer clear of these fraudulent sites."Furthermore, information will be conveyed to the public on the commencement of the recruitment exercise in the mass media," he said.Mr. Dahun said that the 2017 recruitment form would be free of charge whenever registration commenced.(NAN)